^xAF6025^xFFFF77Hello, it's Lazy Exile and it's the POB for my league starter in 3.26
This write up will help you get through the early game as a new players. I have more loads out in this POB for the End Game setup as well.
If you are not familiar with the Campaign Route, use this tool: https://heartofphos.github.io/exile-leveling/ ^xAF6025^xD02090^7_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________^7^7^7
^x70FF70Act 1 - 3 | ^x70FF70Choose the Loadout ^xE05030^xFAA4BDPre-PS Totem ^x70FF70in Top Right ^xD02090^7_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________^7^7^7^7
^4TREE ^xB0DB9C> 1 - 12, 12 - 18, 18 - 25, 25 - 32 available, change to it to see priority pathing > Grab ^xE05030Runebinder^7 ^xB0DB9Cwhen you get ArmaBrand (Level 28+)
^xFFFF77SKILLS ^xB0DB9C> Skills are breakdown into Gems, Support Gems and when do you get them to make it easier to follows.^ ^xB0DB9C> Click on the skill to see the link^7
^x70FF70^xFFFF77^xFFFF77CRAFT 2x WANDS FOR PS TOTEM SWAP^7 ^x8888FF^7 ^xCAE8BD> 1. Buy/Pick up any Spiral Wands (Add # Lightning Damage to Spell and Attack) and make it magic by^7 x1^7 ^x8888FFOrb of Transmutation^7 ^7- ^xCAE8BD Clarrisa in Act 3 should sell it^7^7 ^x8888FF^7 ^xCAE8BD> 2. Buy a Chain belt and make it magic by^7 x1 ^x8888FFOrb of Transmutation^7^7^7^7 ^x8888FF^7 ^xCAE8BD> 3. Sell to Vendor^7 x1 ^x8888FFMagic^7 Wand + x1 ^x8888FFMagic^7 Chain belt + x1 Whetstone^7^7 ^xB0DB9C^x70FF70 > You'll get a Spiral Wand with % Increased Spell Damage that is good for the PS Swap^7
^xD02090^7^xFFFF77NORMAL LAB^7 ^xB0DB9C> At level 32, go do Normal Lab and prepare to swap into PS Totem > Get ^xE05030Conviction of Power^7 ^xB0DB9Cas 1st ascendancy point > Buy gem in Library or at least Power Siphon to add quality to it after finish Lab^7
^xFFFF77BANDITS^7 ^xB0DB9C > Alira for elemental resistance is good (require respec later) > I choose to kill all bandits to get 1 extra passive point^7
^xFFFF77ITEMS^7 ^xCAE8BD> Regex for shop: ^7^xE05030b-b-r|b-[br]-b|r-b-b|b-b|r-b|b-r|nne|rint^7 ^xB0DB9C> Look for a shield for Shield Charge > Look for Wands/Scepters with Fire Damage ^7_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________^7^7^7^7
^x70FF70Act 3 - End of Campaign | ^x70FF70Choose the Loadout ^xE05030^xFAA4BDPS Swap ^x70FF70in Top Right ^xD02090^7_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________^7^7^7^7
^xD02090^xFFFF77GEM LEVELING ^xCAE8BD> Level your Gems at "The Docks" by kiling monsters there after buying them in Library^xFFFF77
RESPEC ^xCAE8BD > Go to Kingsmarch -> Talk to Fautus to respec the point once you swap to PS Totem > Unspec ^xE05030Runebinder^7, ^xE05030Explosive Impact^7, ^xCAE8BDand^7 ^xE05030Templar starting Area^7
^xD02090^xFFFF77CRUEL LAB^7 ^xB0DB9C> At level 55, go do Cruel Lab > Get ^xE05030Pursuit of Faith ^xB0DB9Cas 2nd ascendancy point > Add quality to Power Siphon by the end of Lab > If you can get ^xAF6025PISCATOR'S VIGIL^7^xCAE8BD, you can also clear Merc Lab easily^7
^x70FF70^xFFFF77GEARING STATS^7 ^xCAE8BD > Life & Mana > Added Lightning Damage to Attack > Fix Strength & Dex > Bench craft Resist to cap resistance > 2x Amethyst ring to cap chaos resistance^7 _______________________________________________________________________________________________________________^7^7^7
^xFAA4BD^x70FF70After Campaign | Choose the Loadout^7 ^xFAA4BD^xFFE99ATransition to Map ^xD02090^7_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________^7^7^7^7
^xFFFF77GEARING^7 ^xADAA47^xCAE8BD > After level 60, you should go and buy ^xAF6025PISCATOR'S VIGIL^7^7 ^xCAE8BDand ^xAF6025MIND OF THE COUNCIL^7^xCAE8BD ^xE05030^xFFFF77ASAP^7^7 ^xCAE8BDThese 2 items will easily triple or quadruple your damage.^xAF6025
^xFFFF77AURA^7 ^xCAE8BD > Swap your Aura setup after Act 10 Kitava to Purity of Elements > Keep Vitality at lower level to reserve less than 10% of Life (otherwise your Mana will drain to 0)
^xD02090^xFFFF77MERC LAB^7^7 ^xB0DB9C> At level 55, go do Cruel Lab > Get ^xE05030Ritual of Awakening ^xB0DB9Cas 3rd ascendancy point > Add quality to Power Siphon by the end of Lab
^2^xFFFF77UPGRADE PRIORITY^7 ^x70FF70Your gears should focus on the following stats:^7 ^xCAE8BD > 1. Cap Resistance (on League start Chaos cap is less important) > 2. Life & Mana > 3. Added Lightning Damage to Attack (Gloves) > 4. Fix Strength & Dex > 5. Malachai's Loop & 1 +1 to Min Power Charge craft on Ring is great^7
_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________^7^7^7
^x70FF70DIfferent Endgame Loadouts | ^xFAA4BD^xDDF6D2Mid Budget & the Rest ^xD02090^7_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________^7^7^7^7
^xFAA4BD^xDDF6D2Mid Budget > 10+ Divines - Should be able to T16 8 modded maps with ease > Run all map mods (beside reflect until you get Woke Ele)
^xB0DB9CExpensive Evasion Setup > 30+ Divines - Should be tanky enough for T17 Farming (but I would at this point spend the currency somewhere) > Could also be Cheaper Depending on the Market
^xB0DB9CExpensive Block Setup > 50+ Divines - I think Svalin will be rarer and therefore more expensive. Lucky block if unchange will still be very good > If you want to push into Endgame Mageblood Setup, you can start with Svalin or go with Expensive Evasion first if gear are cheaper
^xB6F500Endgame Doryani Setup > 300+ Divines upward due to scarcity of items, but is very strong and capable of Uber Bossing
^x00FFDEMageblood Setup > 600+ Divines setup, should be able to clear all contents at this point > In term of investment, Totem Build is hard to invest in defense so unless you really like Totem, and have a Mageblood ready... ^7_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________ ^x70FF70^xFFFF77My discord if you have any questions:^7^7 https://discord.gg/ccK7ZP3CRB ^xFFFF77Link to Video Guide:^7 https://youtu.be/lfHe0n_rdaA
